should be in no rush to play this move, however. In fact, he might as well wait
until Black plays ... a7-a6, as in the previous game. 8. tt'lc3 is the main move
here, when after} 9.Nb3 d6 10.Bf4 {1O..!f4 e5 11.. !g5 (note the similarities to
the previous game) 11... f6 12.. !e3 tt'lf5 13. i.d2 tt'lc6 14. tt'ld5 tt'lh6?!
15. i.e3 (targeting b6) 15 .. .f5 16.. ib6 Ш7 17. c5!, White crashed through in
the center in H.Saldano Dayer-L.Sanchez Delgado, La Roda 2007. White was patient
about getting in c4-c5 this game, and it paid off. 8... tOa6 8.. . tt'lbc6,
followed by ... b7-b6 after White moves his knight, was better. Black has more
chances to generate counterplay this way. If the second player is able to
quickly work in ... b7-b6, this is a sign that "White has played c4-c5 too soon.
9. £b3 My hopes of tt'ld4-b5-d6 were dashed, but I was still confident about my
prospects of carrying out this maneuver with my other knight. 9.. .©c7 Now I can
