ttJxcl 25. 'I1Bxe6+ <&h8 26. E:xc1 ti'e7 defends against "White’s threats. 23_
.ia6? Black should be more stubborn. 23... 'I1Bd6, holding onto the pawn, was
better. 24. ttJd3 .ia6 25. 'I1Bxb4 (or 25. ttJxb4 .ixfl 26. E:xc3 .ic4 27.
'I1Bb2 E:ca7) 25... 'I1Bxb4 26. ttJxb4.ixfl27.<.ixfl b5 intending ...E:c4 leaves
Black at least equal, if not better. 24. ti'xb4 Now White has emerged with a
slight plus thanks to his pressure against b6. 24. •• ttJxa2 ?? 24.. .'I1Bc8
would have left Black only a little worse. 25. Ybb6 Threatening to take on e6.
